QUESTION:
Nautilus developers are actively working on one of the project repositories, /usr/src/kodekloudrepos/official. 
They recently decided to implement some new features in the application, and they want to maintain those new changes in a separate branch. 
Below are the requirements that have been shared with the DevOps team:

On Storage server in Stratos DC create a new branch xfusioncorp_official from master branch in /usr/src/kodekloudrepos/official git repo.

Please do not try to make any changes in code.



SOLUTIONS:
Change the server to storage server
ssh natasha@ststor01

Change directory to root
#sudo su

Change to the git directory
# cd /usr/src/kodekloudrepos/official
 
List out all the branches in the git
# git branch
* kodekloud_official
  master
  
 
 Change the branch to master in order to create a branch according to the task
  # git checkout master
Switched to branch 'master'

Create a new branch
# git checkout -b xfusioncorp_officialSwitched to a new branch 'xfusioncorp_official'


Validate by listing our all the branches
# git branch
  kodekloud_official
  master
* xfusioncorp_official
